Section Element

<section> defines elements in a document, such as 
chapters, headings, or any other area of the document 
with the same theme.


<section>
  <h2>Fun Facts About Cricket</h2> 
  <p>A single match of cricket can last up to 5 days.</p>
</section>


///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////


Article Element

The <article> element holds content such as articles, 
blogs, comments, magazines, etc. Subheaders can be enclosed
in these elements as well.

- might contain a combination of text, images, audio, etc.


<section>
  <h2>Fun Facts About Cricket</h2>
  <article>
    <p>A single match of cricket can last up to 5 days.</p>
  </article>
</section>